Shout out to @africamagic for helping me grow from being a presenter, to producer in 2015. This was the first show I produced. It was called “Highlites With Ik”. It was a Late Night Style talk show. We filmed in-front of a live studio audience of about 225 people every week. And it was so much fun. Not one audience member was paid to be there. 
I learnt so much through this process. And I gained the best crew in the world. A lot of whom still work with us on our current show Comedy Nites. 
I’m just grateful for my process.

Hey people, the elections are over. But we still have serious questions to ask ourselves.
Just a quick word to commend a few people. 
Also please remember Lagos today is only special because of “Industry” and you don’t need to be a genius to figure out that the wealth of lagos was not created by only the Yorubas. No body should be made to feel unwelcome here. If all the non- Yoruba people left lagos with their businesses, what would Lagos be like? Let us stop making statements that are oppressive and divisive. Let us rather develop a National outlook to our identities, where we are all Nigerians. No great nation was built on ideals of tribalism. Great nations are built when people appreciate the various parts (states) that make up the whole. Let’s stop this “Third World” behaviour.

I’m calling it Day 1 but it’s really not Day 1 at all for anyone on the production. By this day the various teams have been planning for months on their own. Putting a show like the AMVCAs together is great deal of work. Shout out to the team at @africamagic for making it happen. 
But yeah, after all the planning in isolation, all the units eventually get together. Each team has a goal and we have to negotiate, discuss and sometimes fight to make each team’s goal fit into the ‘major goal’ A Fantastic AMVCA. It’s this meeting of teams that I’m referring to as Day 1. 
Luckily, @zozitunzi and I had met on another job a few years ago so it didn’t take much to work out our chemistry. 
#AMVCA
#AMVCA9
#Planning

Day 2 is kinda interesting. Teams have met, fought, made peace and are working on synergy. It’s also a good day to eat well. It’s usually the last day for a decent meal before the actual show (Trust me). It’s also the last day any major changes can be made to the show.

Day 3 is mostly about getting your mind in the right space. Keeping positive thoughts going. Some things will go wrong and other things will not work out as planned but determine that it’s going to be an awesome show. You’ve done the work. Now trust the team. And most importantly TRUST YOURSELF.

This year I got on the Red Carpet really early (4:15pm). I didn’t want to come through the rushing crowd that happens just before the show starts.

Before I go on to post my looks for the main show, I have to take a minute to give props to @maiatafo who has basically clothed me since I started hosting the AMVCAs. He doesn’t just send me the looks. He jealously and meticulously takes time to make sure they come out right. When you realise just how many people he dresses for the AMVCAs, you’ll appreciate the amount of time it takes to achieve such attention to detail. 
He also comes backstage at different times to check on me and quite literally helps me get changed in those very short advert breaks. 
Thank you @maiatafo. 
When I host The Oscars or attend the Met Gala I’ll probably be wearing. @atafo.official.

Finally getting around to posting my AMVCA looks. All of these were designed by @atafo.official. Interesting fact, @maiatafo has got my sizing down to perfection. He could make me a suit in his sleep and it would fit perfectly. (No jokes)
Have you got a favorite?

Ps: @maiatafo what was the name of the material the pants for looks 1&3 were made from again? It sweets me when you say it. 😂

Seems like I made you wait forever, but I’m ready to bring you another edition of The Ik Talks (2 actually)

For those of you who are kinda just starting out, and everyone else who has ever asked me to Mentor them I’ve got a Mentorship Class from 11am to 1pm. And that is free to attend

Then for those who may have been at this for a few years already and are trying to take the business to another level, we’ll have an Exclusive Masterclass. It will be far more detailed. The masterclass will cost you N50,000 and will hold from 4pm - 7pm (also on the 22nd of October)

Whichever class you choose to come for, I look forward to meeting you and helping you get the “Business” in Show-Biz

If you’re not in media or showbiz but work a 9-5 that involves presentations and public speaking, I’ll be glad to help you too if you sign up. 

The venue is Alliance Française Ikoyi.
You can find registration links in my bio.
